Just a question here. So you're going to boycott Target and have to shop somewhere else to buy your goods? Have you looked into the company's history on other major issues? Some of these other chain stores discriminate against women, minorities, etc. All I'm saying is before you stop spending your money at one store and take your business elsewhere, do your homework. You may be trading a lesser evil for a greater evil. Don't be so quick to judge and jump on the flavor of the day. Think about it.
